org.archive.wayback.replay

Class RangeResource

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.InputStream
      • org.archive.wayback.core.Resource
        • org.archive.wayback.replay.RangeResource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class RangeResource
extends Resource
    RangeResource decorates Resource to render partial content response to range request. After constructing with wrapped Resource and requested range, call parseRange() to prepare internal state for rendering. The method will throw RangeNotSatisfiableException if the requested byte ranges cannot be replayed with the base Resource. RangeResource currently only works with:
    • A single-range request
    • A 200 capture with Content-Length, or a valid 206 capture with single range (i.e. no support for multipart/byteranges)
    See Also:
    HttpHeaderOperation.parseRanges(String)

      • availableRange

        protected long[] availableRange()
        Look at resource HTTP header fields and determine the byte range available.
        Returns:
        array with three long values:
        1. offset of first available byte,
        2. offset of last available byte + 1,
        3. instance-length
        Note this method returns null for multipart/byteranges response.
